<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4561] Ordering of operations in StreamThread.shutdownTasksAndState may void at-least-once guarantees</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4561</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;shutdownTasksAndState&lt;/tt&gt; we currently commit offsets as the first step. If a subsequent step throws an exception, i.e, flushing the producer, then this would violate the at-least-once guarantees.&lt;br/&gt;
We need to commit after all other state has been flushed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13029399">KAFKA-4561</key>
            <summary>Ordering of operations in StreamThread.shutdownTasksAndState may void at-least-once guarantees</summary>
